# Curated CA trust anchors for dial-idf embedded TLS verification.
#
# Why curated instead of the full esp_crt_bundle: on this IDF v6.0 toolchain
# build, esp_crt_bundle is broken, so we embed a small set of PEM roots
# directly (EMBED_TXTFILES, exposed via dial_oauth_root_ca()) and verify
# against them with mbedtls. mbedtls parses a concatenated PEM file into a
# list of independent trust anchors, so this file is simply the roots below
# back to back -- lines outside a BEGIN/END block (like this header and the
# one-line labels before each cert) are ignored by the PEM parser.
#
# Roots included and why:
#   - GlobalSign Root CA (R1) + GTS Root R4: current Orion (mcp.orionsleep.com)
#     chain as observed live.
#   - GTS Root R1: Google Trust Services' primary RSA root, kept alongside
#     R4 as headroom in case Orion's chain is re-issued under it.
#   - ISRG Root X1: Let's Encrypt, common for self-hosted/small-vendor APIs.
#   - USERTrust RSA + USERTrust ECC Certification Authority: Sectigo, the
#     github.com chain.
#   - DigiCert Global Root CA + DigiCert Global Root G2: GitHub's assets/
#     objects CDN (objects.githubusercontent.com) has historically chained
#     through DigiCert.
#   - Amazon Root CA 1: AWS-hosted APIs.
#
# This set exists to survive a routine Orion CA rotation without bricking
# device provisioning/control, and to support planned OTA-from-GitHub
# (github.com + objects.githubusercontent.com) without another firmware
# push. Extracted from the macOS Homebrew OpenSSL trust store
# (/opt/homebrew/etc/openssl@3/cert.pem) on 2026-07-09; each cert verified
# individually (openssl x509 -noout -subject -enddate) and the resulting
# chains verified live against mcp.orionsleep.com, github.com, and
# objects.githubusercontent.com.

